OL,3,CWhat is a supermajority and why do the
OL,4,CTories keep talking about it?
OL,6,FIn Scotland, some laws, particularly
OL,7,Fthose affecting the election of MSPs
OL,8,F(Members of the Scottish Parliament),
OL,9,Frequire a supermajority, meaning two-
OL,10,Fthirds of MSPs must vote in favour.
OL,12,FPolicing Minister Chris Philp said in
OL,13,Fan interview that an "enormous
OL,14,Fmajority" would mean winning by dozens
OL,15,For even hundreds of seats. With 650
OL,16,Fseats in the Commons, a party would
OL,17,Fneed 434 seats to hold a two-thirds
OL,18,Fmajority, a margin of 218 seats.
