OL,3,CWhat is a supermajority and why do the
OL,4,CTories keep talking about it?
OL,6,FHowever, in theory, a British
OL,7,Fgovernment with a majority of 10 MPs
OL,8,Fis no different from one with a
OL,9,Fmajority of 100 MPs, as both can
OL,10,Fcontrol the legislative agenda and
OL,11,Fpass laws with a majority vote.
OL,13,FBut, narrow majorities are vulnerable
OL,14,Fto rebellions by backbenchers or
OL,15,Funexpected by-elections. Larger
OL,16,Fmajorities help party leaders lessen
OL,17,Fthe impact of these threats.
