OL,3,CWhat is a supermajority and why do the
OL,4,CTories keep talking about it?
OL,6,FAs the second-largest party in the
OL,7,FCommons, the opposition often
OL,8,Fstruggles to defeat government-backed
OL,9,Fmotions. Instead, it scrutinises
OL,10,Flegislation through debates and its
OL,11,Fpresence on various committees
OL,12,Foverseeing departments.
OL,14,FHowever, a larger majority means fewer
OL,15,FMPs from the opposition are available
OL,16,Ffor scrutiny.
