OL,3,CWhat is a supermajority and why do the
OL,4,CTories keep talking about it?
OL,6,FIn 1997, Tony Blair secured 418 seats
OL,7,Fout of a possible 659, giving Labour a
OL,8,Fgovernment with a substantial majority
OL,9,Fof 179.
OL,11,FThis decisive victory enabled the
OL,12,Fparty to implement significant and
OL,13,Fenduring reforms, such as establishing
OL,14,Fthe minimum wage and devolving powers
OL,15,Fto Scotland, Wales, and Northern
OL,16,FIreland.
OL,18,FAfter his initial landslide victory,
OL,19,FBlair secured smaller majorities in
OL,20,Ffuture elections, standing at 167 in
OL,21,F2001 and 66 in 2005.
